#open-question(title: [Prospective Cohort of Psychologization → Functional Decline])[
The single most important evidence gap: no longitudinal study has prospectively measured psychologization exposure and tracked functional decline with adequate confounder control. Büchner 2025 is cross-sectional (n=1,156); all other cited studies are qualitative or cross-sectional. Proposed: n ≥ 500 newly diagnosed, 36-month follow-up, quarterly assessments including psychologization exposure, SF-36, actigraphy, PEM frequency, CPET, and biomarker panel. Primary analysis: mixed-effects model testing baseline psychologization as predictor of functional trajectory after controlling for objective severity measures.
] <oq:psychologization-prospective-cohort>
